# Re-push mid-check cancels and re-tests (Invariant 5): re-pushing the same
# ref (a new SHA) while a check is gated cancels the in-flight run and
# discards its verdict. The ref is not parked — it naturally re-queues and a
# fresh trial starts on the new SHA, landing normally from there. A run
# present at the start of a tick claims that whole tick, so the cancellation
# and the re-queue are observed on two separate ticks. Ports
# TestReconcile_CandidateMovedMidCheck / TestIntegration_RepushMidCheck.

push-candidate main alice widget files/v1
tick                             # trial starts; "test" is gated, in flight

repush main alice widget files/v2  # re-push: new SHA, same ref, mid-check
tick                                # detects the move; cancels + Skips the old run

assert-event skipped
! assert-slot-gone main alice widget  # not parked: the ref still exists, just re-queued
! assert-event landed

tick                              # next tick: not parked, so it re-queues on the new SHA

await-started test
release-check test passed         # green: land the re-pushed candidate

assert-event landed
assert-target-is-merge main
assert-slot-gone main alice widget

-- files/v1/.gauntlet.kdl --
check "test" {
    command "true"
}
-- files/v1/NOTES.md --
original push
-- files/v2/.gauntlet.kdl --
check "test" {
    command "true"
}
-- files/v2/NOTES.md --
re-push while test was running
